50|$|The Sumatran striped rabbit (Nesolagus netscheri), {{also known}} as the <b>Sumatra</b> <b>short-eared</b> <b>rabbit</b> or Sumatran rabbit, is a rabbit found only in forests in the Barisan Mountains in western Sumatra, Indonesia and {{surrounding}} areas. It is threatened by habitat loss, leading the IUCN to rate it as Vulnerable.|$|E
50|$|The Ili pika {{somewhat}} {{resembles a}} <b>short-eared</b> <b>rabbit.</b> It is large for a pika, with {{a length of}} 20.3-20.4 cm and a weight of up to 250 g. It has brightly colored hair and displays large rusty-red spots on forehead, crown, and {{the sides of the}} neck.|$|R

